# ThreatForge Output — SIGNATURES
# CVE:       CVE-2026-57898
# Product:   mongodb server
# Tags:      [RCE] [CRIT]
# Score:     70
# Tier:      HIGH PRIORITY
# Generated: 2026-07-21T04:24:24.088584Z
# Status:    OK
# ---

# Confidence: No public PoC known — pattern inferred from the CVE/advisory
# description only [2]. The rule targets HTTP PUT/POST requests to the Eclipse
# BaSyx AAS thumbnail API endpoint with path-traversal sequences in the URI,
# consistent with CWE-22 arbitrary file write via improper filename handling [2].
# No packet-capture (PCAP) data source is available to this pipeline — this
# pattern is NOT verified against captured exploit traffic.
# NOTE: This is a proposed draft for analyst review. The endpoint path and
# traversal pattern are inferred from the advisory description; if the actual
# BaSyx API path differs, the content matches MUST be updated before deployment.
# CVE-2026-57898 — Eclipse BaSyx Java Server SDK 2.0.0-milestone-05 through
# 2.0.0-milestone-12, MongoDB backend, unauthenticated arbitrary file write
# via AAS thumbnail API (CVSS 9.0 CRITICAL [1], no authentication required [2]).

alert http $EXTERNAL_NET any -> $HOME_NET any (
  msg:"THREATFORGE CVE-2026-57898 Eclipse BaSyx AAS thumbnail arbitrary file write attempt";
  flow:established,to_server;
  http.method; content:"PUT"; nocase;
  http.uri; content:"/submodels"; nocase;
  http.uri; content:"thumbnail"; nocase;
  http.uri; pcre:"/(?:%2F|%5C|\/|\\\)\.\.(?:%2F|%5C|\/|\\)/i";
  reference:cve,2026-57898;
  metadata:mitre_technique_id T1190, is_kev false, status experimental;
  classtype:attempted-admin; sid:9000004; rev:1; )

